Question:
Calculate the sum of only the odd numbers.

Input:
List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);

Solutions :- 

Java 8 Streams sum odd numbers using filter(odd) → mapToInt → sum(). For input [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], sums 1+3+5=9.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream → filter(n -> n % 2 != 0) → mapToInt(Integer::intValue) → sum().

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class SumOddNumbers {
    public static int sumOdds(List<Integer> nums) {
        return nums.stream()
                   .filter(n -> n % 2 != 0)
                   .mapToInt(Integer::intValue)
                   .sum();
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);
        System.out.println(sumOdds(nums));  // 9
    }
}

#Thought Process
Predicate: n % 2 != 0 identifies odds (works for negatives too).
Primitive optimization: mapToInt avoids boxing for summation.
Terminal: sum() reduces IntStream to int. Single-pass O(n).

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: Returns 0 (sum identity)
No odds: Returns 0
All odds: Sums all elements
Zero: Even (0 % 2 == 0), filtered out
Negatives: -3 % 2 == -1 != 0, correctly odd
Null list: NPE on stream()
Null elements: NPE in intValue()
